I completely agree.  And NT is very standard, even out of the box.  It
slips in to TCP/IP networks with ease, and supports LOTS of
industry standards.  So it doesn't shop with NFS or a telnetd included.
They're all available (or nearly so).  Same with "X".  It's very
interoperable.


